1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,639
James chapter number one this morning,

2
00:00:01,639 --> 00:00:04,119
we'll be looking at verses 19 through 27.

3
00:00:04,119 --> 00:00:06,639
And really, as we look at this portion of scripture,

4
00:00:06,639 --> 00:00:09,380
you're reminded our theme, as it's on the banners,

5
00:00:09,380 --> 00:00:12,520
we sing the theme song, it's all over the place

6
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:15,539
for us to be reminded throughout the year

7
00:00:15,539 --> 00:00:17,120
that we're studying through the book of James

8
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:20,040
and our theme is doers of the word.

9
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:22,360
And in this portion of scripture this morning

10
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:25,200
that we'll look at, we'll come to that theme verse

11
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,479
for the calendar year, James one and verse 22,

12
00:00:28,479 --> 00:00:32,959
but be doers of the word and not hearers only,

13
00:00:32,959 --> 00:00:36,159
deceiving your own selves.

14
00:00:36,159 --> 00:00:38,319
I've titled the message simply this morning,

15
00:00:38,319 --> 00:00:40,720
hearing and doing.

16
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:42,520
I believe as the first chapter here

17
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:45,360
of the book of James closes, there's an emphasis

18
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:47,080
that is placed upon the importance

19
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:50,840
of applying God's word in our lives.

20
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:53,000
The reality is that as Baptists,

21
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,680
we claim that the Bible is our sole authority

22
00:00:56,759 --> 00:00:59,799
for faith and practice.

23
00:00:59,799 --> 00:01:03,319
And what we believe, we ought to be able to defend

24
00:01:03,319 --> 00:01:05,559
from the pages of this book.

25
00:01:05,559 --> 00:01:08,199
Why do you believe what you believe?

26
00:01:08,199 --> 00:01:10,959
And we open the Bible and say that God's word

27
00:01:10,959 --> 00:01:15,760
is authoritative and it gives us truth for living.

28
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:19,000
Not only for doctrine, for the things that we believe,

29
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,360
but also for practice.

30
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:23,559
Why we behave the way that we do.

31
00:01:23,559 --> 00:01:25,760
Why do we live the way that we live,

32
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:29,480
seeking to please honor and glorify the Lord.

33
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:33,519
And we find that historically at various times of history,

34
00:01:33,519 --> 00:01:37,279
the Baptists were referred to being people of the book.

35
00:01:37,279 --> 00:01:39,720
And by the way, that's a good term, amen.

36
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:43,239
To be categorized as this group of people,

37
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:45,199
we weren't always called Baptists.

38
00:01:45,199 --> 00:01:48,080
There were various terms that were applied

39
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:50,339
to those that held to the distinctives

40
00:01:50,339 --> 00:01:52,319
that we still hold to today.

41
00:01:52,319 --> 00:01:55,699
But they were often referred to as being people

42
00:01:56,540 --> 00:01:57,379
of the book.

43
00:01:57,379 --> 00:01:59,739
In fact, as you read this portion of scripture,

44
00:01:59,739 --> 00:02:02,220
and we'll get through the entirety of it this morning,

45
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:06,099
I believe that you are easily reminded of the words

46
00:02:06,099 --> 00:02:07,739
of the Lord Jesus Christ.

47
00:02:07,739 --> 00:02:10,100
In fact, I wanna read for you just a portion.

48
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,619
You don't need to turn there, but if you'd like to,

49
00:02:11,619 --> 00:02:13,660
it's Matthew chapter number seven.

50
00:02:13,660 --> 00:02:16,020
And I wanna remind you of what Jesus said

51
00:02:16,020 --> 00:02:19,139
as we have recorded here in Matthew seven,

52
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:20,699
in verses 24 through 29.

53
00:02:20,699 --> 00:02:23,820
Because really as we read the latter parts

54
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:25,820
of James chapter number one,

55
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:27,899
I believe that even as you read it,

56
00:02:27,899 --> 00:02:32,419
that you are reminded of the words of the Lord Jesus Christ

57
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:34,419
as he's speaking and preaching here

58
00:02:34,419 --> 00:02:36,020
as it's recorded in Matthew seven.

59
00:02:36,020 --> 00:02:37,539
Look in verse 24.

60
00:02:37,539 --> 00:02:42,539
Jesus said, therefore, whosoever heareth these sayings

61
00:02:42,539 --> 00:02:47,539
of mine and doeth them, I will liken him unto a wise man,

62
00:02:49,339 --> 00:02:52,740
which built his house upon a rock.

63
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:56,899
The rain descended and the floods came and the winds blew

64
00:02:56,899 --> 00:03:01,020
and beat upon the house, that house, and it fell not.

65
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:01,940
Why?

66
00:03:01,940 --> 00:03:05,460
For it was founded upon a rock.

67
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:09,059
And everyone that heareth these sayings of mine

68
00:03:09,059 --> 00:03:14,059
and doeth them not shall be likened unto a foolish man,

69
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:18,539
which built his house upon the sand.

70
00:03:18,539 --> 00:03:21,220
The rain descended and the floods came,

71
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:26,220
the winds blew and beat upon that house and it fell.

72
00:03:26,419 --> 00:03:28,660
And great was the fall of it.

73
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:32,500
It came to pass when Jesus had ended these sayings,

74
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,020
the people, notice what it says,

75
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:37,699
the people were astonished at his doctrine

76
00:03:37,699 --> 00:03:40,139
for he taught them as one,

77
00:03:40,139 --> 00:03:44,899
having authority and not as the scribes.

78
00:03:44,899 --> 00:03:47,580
Our God has all authority and all power.

79
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:51,699
And they saw, they observed, heard the words,

80
00:03:51,699 --> 00:03:54,779
they saw there's something different about the teaching

81
00:03:54,779 --> 00:03:56,460
of the Lord Jesus Christ.

82
00:03:56,460 --> 00:03:59,179
And here we find and we sing songs

83
00:03:59,179 --> 00:04:01,580
with the Sunday school kids about the wise man

84
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:03,259
built his house upon the rock.

85
00:04:03,259 --> 00:04:05,279
And you find that that's derived

86
00:04:05,279 --> 00:04:06,619
from this portion of scripture.

87
00:04:06,619 --> 00:04:09,179
And there's a wise man and a foolish man.

88
00:04:09,179 --> 00:04:13,899
And the reality is that as you study here in Matthew 7,

89
00:04:13,899 --> 00:04:17,019
both groups of people heard the same teaching

90
00:04:17,019 --> 00:04:20,820
from the same teacher, the Lord Jesus Christ.

91
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:22,459
He's God in flesh.

92
00:04:22,459 --> 00:04:24,839
He's the best teacher, the best preacher

93
00:04:24,839 --> 00:04:27,140
that's ever walked upon the face of the earth.

94
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:29,299
And it said, here are these sayings,

95
00:04:29,299 --> 00:04:30,959
notice what it says, of mine.

96
00:04:32,019 --> 00:04:34,299
And we find that they both heard,

97
00:04:34,299 --> 00:04:37,619
both groups of people heard the same message.

98
00:04:37,619 --> 00:04:40,579
It wasn't in the hearing, it was in the responding.

99
00:04:40,579 --> 00:04:44,959
It was that one group heard and applied, they were doers.

100
00:04:44,959 --> 00:04:47,040
They took and applied the truth.

101
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:51,519
And Jesus said, I'm gonna liken them to a wise man.

102
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:56,059
But the other group, they heard, but they did not apply.

103
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,559
They did not do.

104
00:04:58,559 --> 00:05:02,480
And Jesus says, I'm gonna liken them to a foolish man.

105
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:05,359
The reality is I think if every single one of us here

106
00:05:05,359 --> 00:05:07,420
this morning were polled, we'd say,

107
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:10,440
I'd like to be categorized as a wise man,

108
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,839
not as a foolish man.

109
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:17,160
But the desire to be in the category

110
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:20,839
is really dependent upon how we respond

111
00:05:20,839 --> 00:05:23,399
to the truth of God's word.

112
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:27,720
We do not know with certainty that James was present

113
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:31,040
as it's recorded there in Matthew chapter number seven.

114
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,880
I don't know that James was there

115
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:37,640
and heard the teaching of Jesus on that particular day.

116
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,480
But we do understand as I preached

117
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,359
in the very beginning of this calendar year,

118
00:05:41,359 --> 00:05:46,359
looking at who the author, the human penman of this book is

119
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:49,320
I believe that after his conversion

120
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,320
that there were probably many things

121
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:55,160
that he was reminded of that he heard Jesus speak

122
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:57,519
and teach during his earthly ministry.

123
00:05:57,519 --> 00:06:01,600
Because not only did Jesus preach, he ministered publicly,

124
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,720
but no doubt there was some personal ministry

125
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:06,119
that took place.

126
00:06:06,119 --> 00:06:08,279
We find there's interactions, John seven,

127
00:06:08,279 --> 00:06:09,880
between him and his brethren.

128
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,600
And you find those types of things.

129
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,480
And perhaps even as we look here

130
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:16,040
at the end of the first chapter of the book of James,

131
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:18,720
maybe as James is penning these words

132
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,200
under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God,

133
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:25,200
he's even being reminded of hearing the Lord Jesus Christ

134
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:30,119
teach very similar to what he's writing here in James one.

135
00:06:30,119 --> 00:06:33,839
Notice with me in verse 19, back in the book of James

136
00:06:33,839 --> 00:06:35,359
in verse number 19, the Bible says,

137
00:06:35,399 --> 00:06:39,320
wherefore, my beloved brethren,

138
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:42,200
let every man be swift to hear,

139
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:45,279
slow to speak, slow to wrath.

140
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:49,600
For the wrath of man worketh not the righteousness of God.

141
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,279
Wherefore, lay apart all filthiness

142
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:54,880
and superfluity of naughtiness

143
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:58,920
and receive with meekness the engrafted word,

144
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:01,559
which is able to save your souls.

145
00:07:01,559 --> 00:07:06,399
But be doers of the word and not hearers only,

146
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:08,720
deceiving your own selves.

147
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,000
We'll get through verse 27

148
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,920
as we go through the message this morning.

149
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,880
But as we look at this portion of scripture,

150
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,559
we know in verse 19, he says,

151
00:07:15,559 --> 00:07:18,559
wherefore, my beloved brethren.

152
00:07:18,559 --> 00:07:21,119
He said in verse number two of the same chapter,

153
00:07:21,119 --> 00:07:24,019
my brethren, and we've established the fact

154
00:07:24,019 --> 00:07:27,079
that James is writing to those that had been converted,

155
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:29,040
those who have been born again,

156
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,839
to these Jewish believers

157
00:07:30,839 --> 00:07:33,940
that were facing such intense persecution

158
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:35,940
because of all that had transpired.

159
00:07:35,940 --> 00:07:37,359
We read in the book of Acts

160
00:07:37,359 --> 00:07:41,559
with the gospel going forth and the intense persecution

161
00:07:41,559 --> 00:07:44,679
and all that was being dealt with there.

162
00:07:44,679 --> 00:07:48,880
In James' writing, he says, my beloved brethren.

163
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,959
He's writing to those that have been saved

164
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:52,100
by the grace of God.

165
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:55,720
In fact, in verse 18, as we spoke of last week,

166
00:07:55,760 --> 00:08:00,279
as we ended the message, he said this in verse 18,

167
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:05,200
of his own will begat he, notice, us

168
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,519
with the word of truth.

169
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:07,920
And James was not only speaking

170
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,040
about his own personal conversion,

171
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,519
but the conversion of those

172
00:08:11,519 --> 00:08:14,799
that were the original recipients that he's writing to,

173
00:08:14,799 --> 00:08:16,640
these saved people.

174
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:18,359
And it's important that we understand that

175
00:08:18,359 --> 00:08:21,100
as we go through the portion of scripture,

176
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,880
for we find that he's writing to believers.

177
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,920
As we note the passage,

178
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:27,760
if you are taking notes this morning,

179
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,619
I want you to notice first of all with me,

180
00:08:29,619 --> 00:08:31,000
notice the exhortation.

181
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,559
In verses 19 through 22,

182
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:36,280
I find that God gives to us through James

183
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,719
an exhortation to the believers.

184
00:08:38,719 --> 00:08:40,179
I want you to consider first of all,

185
00:08:40,179 --> 00:08:42,559
when we kind of look at this exhortation

186
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:44,280
and kind of break it apart,

187
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:48,000
I want you to see that we must accept the Bible

188
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,119
as being authoritative.

189
00:08:50,119 --> 00:08:53,820
We must accept the Bible as being authoritative.

190
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:55,500
There are many times that I've sat

191
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,760
with individuals in my office.

192
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:59,020
There are many times that I've had conversations

193
00:08:59,020 --> 00:09:01,260
with individuals in various settings.

194
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:04,799
And as we're going to engage in conversation,

195
00:09:04,799 --> 00:09:07,099
as they're going to begin to ask questions

196
00:09:07,099 --> 00:09:08,419
or whatever it may be,

197
00:09:08,419 --> 00:09:10,299
I'll normally start out this way.

198
00:09:10,299 --> 00:09:14,900
Can we first agree that the Bible is the authority?

199
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:18,739
Because if we cannot agree that the Bible is the authority,

200
00:09:18,739 --> 00:09:22,419
then really there's not much point for the conversation.

201
00:09:22,419 --> 00:09:25,099
You end up, well, this thought and this thought

202
00:09:25,099 --> 00:09:27,619
and there's truth, their truth, his truth.

203
00:09:27,619 --> 00:09:30,099
No, there's one truth and it's God's truth.

204
00:09:30,099 --> 00:09:33,140
And Jesus Christ is the truth.

205
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:35,179
And we're thankful that we have a Bible.

206
00:09:35,179 --> 00:09:38,460
And so James here in this exhortation,

207
00:09:38,460 --> 00:09:40,099
I believe that he first is saying,

208
00:09:40,099 --> 00:09:44,559
listen, we must accept that God's word is authoritative.

209
00:09:44,559 --> 00:09:47,979
Now we know at the time of the writing,

210
00:09:47,979 --> 00:09:51,419
the whole canon of scripture has not yet been completed.

211
00:09:51,419 --> 00:09:54,020
But now we live on this side of history

212
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:57,159
where we have the whole canon of scripture.

213
00:09:57,159 --> 00:10:00,059
And I'm so thankful to have the scripture.

214
00:10:00,059 --> 00:10:03,659
the Bible, the word of God, that we can hold it,

215
00:10:03,659 --> 00:10:05,319
we can read it, we can preach it,

216
00:10:05,319 --> 00:10:09,119
we can meditate upon it, we can share it with others,

217
00:10:09,119 --> 00:10:12,999
and God's word is powerful, it is authoritative.

218
00:10:12,999 --> 00:10:15,419
We find that he says this in verse number 21.

219
00:10:15,419 --> 00:10:17,539
Notice, he says, in the middle of the verse,

220
00:10:17,539 --> 00:10:22,539
receive with meekness the engrafted word,

221
00:10:23,179 --> 00:10:27,799
notice what he says, which is able to save your souls.

222
00:10:27,799 --> 00:10:30,039
Now, he's not really talking about salvation,

223
00:10:30,039 --> 00:10:33,439
redemption in this portion of Scripture, in verse 21,

224
00:10:33,439 --> 00:10:35,519
he's not talking about that salvation

225
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:38,039
from the penalty of sin,

226
00:10:38,039 --> 00:10:40,479
he's already talked about that in verse 18.

227
00:10:40,479 --> 00:10:42,039
But I want you to consider this way,

228
00:10:42,039 --> 00:10:45,079
and oftentimes, David in the Psalms will talk about,

229
00:10:45,079 --> 00:10:47,359
he saved me out of all my troubles,

230
00:10:47,359 --> 00:10:49,959
that idea of being delivered.

231
00:10:49,959 --> 00:10:54,079
And let me acknowledge, let us acknowledge this morning,

232
00:10:54,079 --> 00:10:57,379
that when we understand that God's word is authoritative,

233
00:10:57,979 --> 00:11:00,059
and we see the exhortation,

234
00:11:00,059 --> 00:11:03,299
to receive with meekness the engrafted word,

235
00:11:03,299 --> 00:11:08,299
notice he says, which is able to save your souls.

236
00:11:08,619 --> 00:11:12,739
You know, taking the truth of this book and living by it

237
00:11:12,739 --> 00:11:16,379
will save you, deliver you from much trouble.

238
00:11:16,379 --> 00:11:17,220
Amen?

239
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:20,739
And there's a lot of things that can cause trouble.

240
00:11:20,739 --> 00:11:23,779
Our flesh has lust, we've talked about that,

241
00:11:23,779 --> 00:11:26,500
we dealt with that in verses 13 through 15

242
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,019
of this same chapter,

243
00:11:28,019 --> 00:11:30,419
and we find that if we would take the Bible

244
00:11:30,419 --> 00:11:34,059
as being the authority, that God said,

245
00:11:34,059 --> 00:11:38,099
God has given to us, not only by inspiration,

246
00:11:38,099 --> 00:11:41,220
but through providential preservation,

247
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:44,299
and we have the word of God.

248
00:11:44,299 --> 00:11:47,500
And God's word will deliver you,

249
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:52,019
will save you from much trouble in this world.

250
00:11:52,019 --> 00:11:52,860
Amen?

251
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:56,939
The Bible says that the way of the transgressor is hard.

252
00:11:58,019 --> 00:12:00,299
Have you found it to be so?

253
00:12:00,299 --> 00:12:01,939
You start disobeying the Lord,

254
00:12:01,939 --> 00:12:05,139
the Bible says whom the Lord loveth, he chasteneth.

255
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:09,000
By the way, chastisement is a good thing,

256
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,539
it's something we should be thankful for,

257
00:12:10,539 --> 00:12:13,500
it shows and proves that we belong to him

258
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:17,539
and that he loves us, but it's not pleasant.

259
00:12:17,539 --> 00:12:20,580
It's profitable, but it's not pleasant,

